23:31.209 --> 23:32.982
No, another time.

23:33.087 --> 23:35.485
Something's happened.
You'd better go and see.

23:35.589 --> 23:39.865
Why do you always do this?
You always stop in the middle of your stories.

23:53.943 --> 23:56.446
Valentina, come here.
Valentina, come here.

23:56.550 --> 23:59.366
I just saw someone...
someone dancing on the water.

24:01.243 --> 24:02.807
I swear. I swear.

24:03.641 --> 24:06.457
When the lightning flashed,
there was a shadow...

24:07.083 --> 24:09.168
...thrown from those pillars over there.

24:09.272 --> 24:11.671
Do you see that?
Do you see the dancer?

24:11.775 --> 24:15.112
- Yeah, he's river dancing.
- Yeah, he's river dancing. See that?

24:15.946 --> 24:17.928
That's someone hanging!

24:18.762 --> 24:20.743
He must be under this bridge.

24:20.848 --> 24:22.516
Hanging?

24:22.621 --> 24:24.080
Get a rope.

24:24.185 --> 24:26.583
If he's hanging by his neck,
he's already got a rope.

24:26.688 --> 24:27.835
- Get a rope!
- OK.

24:28.773 --> 24:31.693
Slowly, slowly, slowly, slowly!
Percy, Percy! Christ!

24:35.447 --> 24:37.220
All right, all right.

24:37.324 --> 24:39.827
OK, lower, lower, lower. All right.

24:40.661 --> 24:41.913
Stop, stop!

24:42.017 --> 24:43.894
Jesus. Agh. All right. OK.

24:43.998 --> 24:45.771
OK. OK.

24:45.875 --> 24:47.023
OK.

24:47.127 --> 24:48.795
No, I can't... I can't reach him.

24:48.900 --> 24:50.881
Hold on, I'll swing you.

24:52.550 --> 24:54.531
I'm gonna swing you in.

24:55.261 --> 24:57.242
All right, try again.

24:59.224 --> 25:00.788
Whoaagh!

25:04.021 --> 25:06.002
Again, up.

25:08.400 --> 25:09.026
Yes.

25:14.866 --> 25:16.117
I've got him.

25:16.222 --> 25:18.307
Oh, my God, what am I doing? Oh, my God!

25:19.350 --> 25:21.331
Sir, are you all right?

25:21.436 --> 25:23.313
OK, I've got you here.

25:24.043 --> 25:25.398
Get in there.

25:25.503 --> 25:28.527
OK, put your arms round me.
Put your arms round me. Oh, jeez!

25:28.631 --> 25:29.882
OK.

25:29.987 --> 25:31.655
All right.

25:33.220 --> 25:35.097
Come on. Stay with me, mate.

25:35.201 --> 25:37.078
Aarrghh!

25:37.912 --> 25:39.685
You've done it. Brilliant!

25:39.789 --> 25:41.875
- OK, pull him up.
- Pull me up!

25:41.979 --> 25:43.648
Jesus Christ!

26:00.333 --> 26:02.106
Whoagh!

26:02.836 --> 26:04.817
- Are you OK?
- Oh, God!

26:09.510 --> 26:12.325
Why are you fishing dead people
out of the river?

26:12.430 --> 26:14.411
Leave him be, for the love of God!

26:14.515 --> 26:15.662
He's dead!

26:15.767 --> 26:19.416
Let's get the hell out of here
before the fuzz turns up.

26:20.981 --> 26:22.962
Anton, help me.

26:24.005 --> 26:27.238
- Help her.
- All right, I've got him.

26:27.342 --> 26:29.010
Watch your head.

26:29.115 --> 26:31.096
Pull him this way.

26:34.746 --> 26:36.727
No, no, no, Val. It's not gonna work.

26:36.832 --> 26:38.709
It's not gonna work. Watch out.

26:38.813 --> 26:40.899
You don't know where he's been, anyway.

26:41.003 --> 26:42.984
Ready? All clear?

26:44.131 --> 26:44.966
Ohh!

26:46.113 --> 26:47.364
Oh!

26:47.468 --> 26:49.450
- He's alive!
- He was.

26:54.351 --> 26:56.332
What on earth is that?

26:57.271 --> 26:59.252
- We'll put him in the trunk.
- But...

26:59.356 --> 27:01.234
- What?
- The boss said leave him.

27:01.338 --> 27:03.215
He thought he was dead. Come on.

27:12.913 --> 27:14.895
No, no, no. I don't like this.

27:14.999 --> 27:17.397
This just doesn't...
It's none of our business.

27:17.502 --> 27:20.526
What do you suggest, that we leave
him on the side of the road?

27:20.630 --> 27:22.611
Definitely. Let's go.

27:22.716 --> 27:24.071
All right.

27:24.176 --> 27:26.157
Careful.

27:26.261 --> 27:28.243
- Anton, come on!
- Percy!

27:28.347 --> 27:30.328
Percy, you dropped these.

27:31.371 --> 27:32.727
Giddy up!

27:32.831 --> 27:34.812
Val! Val, come on!

27:35.647 --> 27:37.628
Jump up.

28:31.125 --> 28:32.585
Hey, you!

28:32.689 --> 28:35.713
I suppose somebody saves your life
every day of the week.

28:35.817 --> 28:37.382
What?

28:37.486 --> 28:39.884
Is it too much of a bother for a mere thank you?

28:40.719 --> 28:42.596
Who are you?

28:42.700 --> 28:47.601
Percival St Antoine della Touraine
et Sansepolcro da Piemonte III.

28:48.331 --> 28:51.668
And if that seems too difficult,
you can call me Percy.

28:51.773 --> 28:53.233
Where the hell are we?

28:53.337 --> 28:57.821
Geographically, in the northern hemisphere,
socially, on the margins,

28:57.925 --> 28:59.907
and narratively, with some way to go.

29:00.845 --> 29:02.514
And your name is?

29:02.618 --> 29:04.182
Uh...

29:06.268 --> 29:07.936
I can't remember.

29:08.041 --> 29:09.813
That's frigging handy!

29:09.918 --> 29:11.899
Any credit cards?

29:12.003 --> 29:13.672
Are you trying to rob me?

29:13.776 --> 29:15.340
What are you doing?

29:15.445 --> 29:17.426
With your name on them.

29:17.530 --> 29:19.512
Oh, right, er...

29:20.554 --> 29:23.370
Where's my wallet? Where's my phone?
What have you done with it?

29:23.474 --> 29:25.456
- Don't look at us.
- Who are you?

29:25.560 --> 29:27.750
He doesn't remember.

29:27.854 --> 29:32.651
Listen, er... whoever you people are,
and whatever it is you get up to,

29:33.485 --> 29:35.050
I'm cool with it.

29:35.154 --> 29:37.344
I won't tell anyone about it and er...

29:38.178 --> 29:40.055
I'm gonna go now, all right?

29:50.796 --> 29:52.986
It's probably for you.

29:54.863 --> 29:56.219
Oh.

29:56.845 --> 29:58.826
Here's my phone.

29:58.930 --> 30:00.599
<i>There you are.</i>

30:01.224 --> 30:03.206
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

30:12.278 --> 30:13.634
Pity.

30:13.738 --> 30:15.303
I speak Russian.

30:17.284 --> 30:18.952
Oh, hello.

30:19.787 --> 30:21.664
Are you all right?

30:22.811 --> 30:24.479
Yeah.

30:24.584 --> 30:26.565
Yeah, it's just I feel...

30:26.669 --> 30:30.006
I think I need a place to gather
my thoughts for a little bit.

30:30.111 --> 30:31.779
Sorry, mate. Sorry, mate.

30:31.883 --> 30:33.865
Thank you for that but you can't stay.

30:33.969 --> 30:35.325
Why not?

30:35.429 --> 30:37.306
What do you mean? Look at him.

30:37.410 --> 30:39.392
We... We don't know who he is.

30:39.496 --> 30:41.164
We don't know what he's done.

30:41.269 --> 30:43.459
Listen, I haven't done anything, mate.

30:43.563 --> 30:45.127
- All right?
- Oh, right.

30:45.231 --> 30:49.194
I understand where you're coming from,
but understand where I'm coming from.

30:49.298 --> 30:52.427
I don't know my name.
You know, I don't know how I got here.

30:52.531 --> 30:56.702
I don't know who you are or who she is,
and I certainly don't know what that is.

30:56.807 --> 30:58.267
You know?

30:58.371 --> 31:01.395
The last thing I remember
is being whacked in the head,

31:01.499 --> 31:05.671
waking up in that box, in the back of this...
whatever the hell this thing is.

31:05.775 --> 31:07.652
And I just... I just...

31:21.313 --> 31:23.503
Oh, my head!

31:27.674 --> 31:29.343
What the hell's going on here?

31:31.116 --> 31:33.097
I told you to leave him. He was dead.

31:33.201 --> 31:34.974
Well, he isn't and we didn't.

31:35.078 --> 31:37.372
We found him hanging
under the bridge, sir.

31:37.477 --> 31:39.041
- Hanging?
- Yeah.

31:39.145 --> 31:42.274
By his neck till dead, if we had any sense.

31:42.378 --> 31:44.672
We found these in his pockets. Two of these.

31:48.114 --> 31:50.095
The Hanged Man.

31:51.033 --> 31:53.119
Scrumpy, get out of my way.

31:56.978 --> 31:57.812
No.

31:57.916 --> 31:59.897
Signs are all clear.

32:01.357 --> 32:03.339
And those marks!

32:03.443 --> 32:05.633
- I recognise them.
- What marks?

32:05.737 --> 32:08.657
You've been sent by Mr Nick, haven't you?

32:08.761 --> 32:11.681
- Mr Nick?
- I knew it. You know his name.

32:11.786 --> 32:12.516
No.

32:12.620 --> 32:14.914
He's got a proposition for me, hasn't he?

32:15.018 --> 32:16.895
A new wager, perhaps,

32:17.938 --> 32:19.815
or another twist in the game?

32:19.920 --> 32:22.110
He can't help himself, can he?

32:23.048 --> 32:25.655
Thank God! Thank God for that!

32:31.286 --> 32:33.372
Dad says you should work.

32:33.476 --> 32:35.458
Help focus your mind.

32:35.562 --> 32:38.169
I don't know,
it might bring your memory back.

32:38.273 --> 32:41.193
Ah, here we are. Try this.

32:41.297 --> 32:42.966
Thanks.

32:50.996 --> 32:52.873
You can help out front.

32:52.977 --> 32:55.271
Sell tickets or something like that.

32:57.357 --> 32:59.025
What do you think?

32:59.130 --> 33:00.485
Hm?

33:02.258 --> 33:03.718
OK.

33:07.472 --> 33:09.454
So... no name

33:09.558 --> 33:11.435
and now no face?

33:12.269 --> 33:14.042
The mystery thickens.

33:14.146 --> 33:16.128
Get your grubby hands...

33:17.588 --> 33:19.465
All right. That's not necessary.

33:19.569 --> 33:21.967
- Valentina, we got a problem.
- So strange.

33:22.072 --> 33:23.949
Just a complete blank, you know.

33:24.053 --> 33:26.243
I can dress myself.

33:26.347 --> 33:28.224
Let me go, I said!

33:29.476 --> 33:30.831
Let me go!

33:35.524 --> 33:38.027
Ow. Hey, come on.

33:38.131 --> 33:40.112
Doctor.

33:41.781 --> 33:43.658
Oh, God, he's gonna be sick.

33:44.909 --> 33:45.744
Aha!

33:45.848 --> 33:48.038
Is your memory less impaired?

33:48.142 --> 33:50.019
Is it all coming back to you now?

33:50.124 --> 33:51.584
What?

33:52.418 --> 33:55.546
Ah, you're bloody useless.
You're a flaming disaster.

33:55.651 --> 33:57.528
You can't go on. You're drunk.

33:57.632 --> 34:00.760
I'm not drunk! I'm grumpy... Scrumpy.

34:03.993 --> 34:05.349
Er...

34:08.581 --> 34:10.771
L-L-Ladies and gentlemen,

34:10.876 --> 34:12.857
raise your sights for one night only.

34:12.960 --> 34:14.630
Encounter...

34:14.734 --> 34:16.610
Percy, where's George gone?

34:16.715 --> 34:19.947
...the majesty, the beauty,
the miracle that's in each...

34:20.053 --> 34:22.868
Anton, where's George?

34:22.972 --> 34:25.475
Who... Who's George?

34:25.579 --> 34:27.561
I thought we should give him a name.

34:28.603 --> 34:30.481
All right, that's cute.

34:30.585 --> 34:35.172
Saint George, in fact. To be precise.
Well, hello there, darling.

34:35.277 --> 34:38.822
Oh, that's a lovely scarf.
It matches those lovely eyes of yours.

34:39.866 --> 34:43.099
Well, actually, I'm here to sell a show.
Want to see a magic show?

34:43.203 --> 34:45.289
Thank God for that. Not a single customer.

34:45.393 --> 34:47.270
- I'm closing up.
- Let's do that.

34:47.373 --> 34:49.877
He's never not done a show before.

34:54.047 --> 34:55.926
- All right.
- N-n-n-no.

34:56.030 --> 34:58.011
No, what are you doing?

34:58.115 --> 35:00.618
I'm doing my job, mate.
Now, come on, do yours.

35:00.723 --> 35:04.477
Do yours. Go juggle.
You're doing your thing, you look beautiful.

35:04.581 --> 35:07.084
OK. Ladies and...

35:07.188 --> 35:08.752
Well, ladies.

35:08.857 --> 35:14.175
I am very proud to present to you
the one, the only, the extraordinary...

35:14.279 --> 35:16.261
Doctor Parnassus.

35:16.365 --> 35:20.328
âª I'm a little teapot short and stout

35:20.432 --> 35:23.352
âª Here's my handle and here's my spout...

35:23.456 --> 35:25.437
Urgh!

35:26.063 --> 35:27.627
Dad?

35:27.732 --> 35:29.609
This man is drunk!

35:29.713 --> 35:31.903
- Dead drunk!
- Oh, that's disgraceful!

35:32.007 --> 35:34.197
- He's not drunk.
- No, he's not. He's...

35:34.301 --> 35:36.283
- Got a bad cold.
- And you know what?

35:36.387 --> 35:39.620
Despite that, he still went on,
for his audience, for you...

35:39.724 --> 35:42.748
at considerable risk for his health.

35:42.852 --> 35:46.711
And I think that is worthy of a round of applause,
ladies and gentlemen.

35:46.815 --> 35:49.005
- What a man.
- We want our money back.

35:49.109 --> 35:50.569
Every penny.

35:50.674 --> 35:52.551
Well, you...

35:53.594 --> 35:56.305
All right, listen.
You can have your money back.

35:57.035 --> 35:58.808
I understand, but I... Listen.

35:58.912 --> 36:01.519
To tell you the truth, the Doctor's daughter...

36:01.623 --> 36:03.813
I know she looks pretty but she ain't...

36:04.647 --> 36:06.629
She's pretty sick, see?

36:06.733 --> 36:08.610
She needs surgery.

36:08.714 --> 36:12.156
So we're trying to scrounge
all we can get. Otherwise she's gonna...

36:12.260 --> 36:15.180
That's what all this is about -
to try and get money for her.

36:16.327 --> 36:18.204
Do you understand? I mean...

36:19.768 --> 36:21.750
How about this?

36:21.854 --> 36:24.670
We'll give you a free ticket -
no, two free tickets -

36:24.774 --> 36:26.755
if you buy another one at half price.

36:26.860 --> 36:29.154
Er... this offer's only available today.

36:31.865 --> 36:33.742
All right, go on.

36:36.349 --> 36:38.331
- What?
- Oh, nothing.

36:39.373 --> 36:42.606
This offer is only available today.

36:46.256 --> 36:48.237
- He took all that?
- Yeah.

36:48.342 --> 36:50.323
Have you ever seen so much?

36:50.427 --> 36:53.451
That is what lying
through your teeth can get you.

36:53.556 --> 36:55.537
Come on, Anton.

36:55.641 --> 36:58.666
How was he to know that
we're not gonna be here tomorrow?

37:00.543 --> 37:02.315
Hey, maybe my birthday won't be so bad.

37:02.420 --> 37:04.297
Yeah, maybe it won't, actually.

37:04.401 --> 37:07.842
Maybe with George here,
maybe you could get out of this dump.

37:09.719 --> 37:11.597
Go find your ideal home.

37:14.516 --> 37:15.872
Anton.

37:17.541 --> 37:20.252
George! Wrong end of the horse, mate.

37:20.356 --> 37:22.338
What's the...

37:32.662 --> 37:34.956
I should be dead.

37:44.028 --> 37:46.427
You know, you shouldn't drink.

37:46.531 --> 37:48.930
It just flat out doesn't agree with you.

37:49.034 --> 37:51.537
You are so right.

37:51.641 --> 37:53.518
You?

37:53.622 --> 37:55.395
Oh, shit.

37:55.499 --> 37:58.941
Oh, well, what do you want from me this time?
I'll do anything.

37:59.045 --> 38:00.401
I know you will.

38:00.505 --> 38:03.842
By the way, your man lost his memory.

38:03.946 --> 38:05.719
Bloody useless.

38:05.823 --> 38:08.117
- He's not my man.
- What?

38:08.222 --> 38:12.184
No. He's a little toerag named Tony Shepherd.

38:13.957 --> 38:16.043
Just tidying up.

38:16.147 --> 38:18.128
He runs a big charity.

38:18.858 --> 38:20.214
I don't trust him.

38:20.944 --> 38:25.428
- But you don't trust me either, do you?
- Oh, just tell me what you want.

38:25.533 --> 38:27.931
I just thought that last night
when you were so upset

38:28.035 --> 38:30.538
that you could maybe use
a little glimmer of hope.

38:30.642 --> 38:34.292
Maybe you could use a little bet.

38:34.396 --> 38:36.378
What?

38:36.482 --> 38:37.942
It's over, it's over. Finito.

38:38.046 --> 38:41.488
Oh, come on, it's never over.

38:42.218 --> 38:45.972
Come on, what have you got to lose?
Look, you could end up winning.

38:46.076 --> 38:48.057
You could save her.

38:50.456 --> 38:52.542
What do you say? First to five souls?

38:53.584 --> 38:55.461
- First to five?
- Yeah.

38:55.566 --> 38:56.921
No tricks?

38:57.026 --> 38:58.694
- No.
- No, no cheating?

38:58.798 --> 38:59.737
No cheating.

38:59.841 --> 39:01.301
I'd say yes. Deal.

39:01.406 --> 39:04.013
God, I love a betting man.

39:04.117 --> 39:06.203
OK, by her birthday, then.

39:06.307 --> 39:08.810
That's in two days, you bastard.

39:08.914 --> 39:11.417
Do you have any idea
what rotten business we're doing?

39:11.521 --> 39:14.232
Things are gonna pick up.
Sure as eggs is eggs.

39:14.337 --> 39:16.526
- Yeah.
- OK.

39:18.299 --> 39:21.741
- First one to five souls wins.
- I'll kill you, you son of a bitch.

39:21.845 --> 39:23.826
Now that I'd like to see.

39:24.556 --> 39:26.538
Wait!

39:29.770 --> 39:31.126
Oh!

39:40.198 --> 39:42.180
Damn phone.

39:46.038 --> 39:48.020
- Morning, Val.
- Hi, George.

39:54.694 --> 39:56.571
Scrumpy?

39:58.135 --> 39:59.074
Scrumpy?

40:00.951 --> 40:02.828
Oh...

40:07.103 --> 40:08.042
Oh.

40:08.146 --> 40:09.710
Good lord.

40:09.815 --> 40:11.275
Good lord.

40:12.526 --> 40:14.403
Food, food. We got food.

40:14.507 --> 40:18.574
We got bread. We got cheese.
We got vegetables.

40:18.679 --> 40:21.390
And we got... this thing.
Whatever this thing is.

40:21.494 --> 40:24.101
It's all your fault we're eating so well today.

40:25.040 --> 40:27.021
Know how to pluck?

40:27.960 --> 40:29.732
Is that... is that... Bertie?

40:29.837 --> 40:32.027
George thought doves would be better.

40:32.131 --> 40:33.487
- Pluck it.
- Pluck it?

40:33.591 --> 40:35.259
- Yeah.
- How?

40:35.364 --> 40:36.198
Here.

40:36.302 --> 40:38.179
That was my best trick.

40:40.056 --> 40:41.412
Five souls in two days, huh?

40:41.516 --> 40:44.436
Put a sock in it. I'm trying to think.

40:45.375 --> 40:48.920
He's been sent to us for a reason. I know it.

40:49.546 --> 40:51.945
- Cards don't lie.
- No?

41:09.464 --> 41:12.384
Pardonnez-moi.
Monsieur Saint George.

41:13.635 --> 41:15.721
Oh, I worry about you.

41:15.825 --> 41:18.328
Not knowing who you are.

41:18.432 --> 41:22.916
It must be extrÃªmement difficile
pour vous, n'est-ce pas?

41:23.021 --> 41:26.253
Yeah, it really is. It's confusing at times.

41:26.358 --> 41:28.026
- I may be able to help you.
- Really?

41:28.235 --> 41:29.903
Yes. You see this contraption here?

41:30.007 --> 41:31.885
Do the honours, Percy.

41:31.989 --> 41:35.013
Yes.
Now, if you don't mind placing it on your head.

41:35.117 --> 41:37.412
- That's it. Now, you see these wires?
- Yes.

41:37.516 --> 41:40.123
Just hold on to that. That's right.

41:40.227 --> 41:41.687
- All right.
- That's right, now.

41:41.791 --> 41:45.754
Now, I just want you to relax.
And just think of nothing.

41:45.858 --> 41:47.735
That's not gonna be hard considering...

41:47.840 --> 41:49.717
- Shut it!
- I beg your pardon?

41:49.821 --> 41:52.115
Your mouth. Don't breathe.

41:52.324 --> 41:53.888
- Hold your breath.
- Seriously?

41:53.992 --> 41:58.164
Just let the energy flow.
Let it wax and wane.

41:58.268 --> 41:59.936
Think of the earth, the ocean...

42:03.273 --> 42:05.463
That's very good. Very good, very good.

42:06.402 --> 42:08.488
Yes. I need a name.

42:08.592 --> 42:11.095
I need a name. Huh?

42:11.303 --> 42:13.702
Yes, I have a name.

42:13.806 --> 42:14.432
Shepherd.

42:15.579 --> 42:17.560
Anthony Shepherd.

42:17.977 --> 42:19.959
They call you Tony.

42:23.713 --> 42:25.694
That was exhausting.

42:28.405 --> 42:31.847
You used to do good works, I understand.

42:31.951 --> 42:35.809
Erm... something about a charity,

42:35.914 --> 42:37.791
I think.

42:41.024 --> 42:43.422
Yes. Erm...

42:44.256 --> 42:46.238
Tony Shepherd...

42:47.385 --> 42:49.679
It rings a bell for sure.

42:49.783 --> 42:51.973
Wow. This...

42:52.495 --> 42:54.476
This... this... It really works.

42:54.580 --> 42:56.457
You erm...

42:56.562 --> 43:00.941
Is there anything else you discovered
when you were doing your "ums"...?

43:01.046 --> 43:02.401
Well, I mean...

43:02.506 --> 43:04.904
You must understand
this is an ancient technique.

43:05.008 --> 43:08.345
- Right.
- I'm extremely rusty, I'm afraid.

43:10.848 --> 43:13.351
No. There was absolutely nothing else.

43:13.455 --> 43:14.811
No.

43:18.252 --> 43:20.234
Well, it's fascinating stuff.

43:20.338 --> 43:23.675
It really is, I must say.
I mean, can I take this off now?

43:23.779 --> 43:25.656
- Yes.
- Is that all right?

43:25.761 --> 43:29.515
- I mean, thank you very much.
- No, no. Not at all. Not at all.

43:29.619 --> 43:31.496
Bless you. I have a name.

43:31.600 --> 43:33.477
Charity work?

43:33.582 --> 43:34.729
Cool.

43:34.833 --> 43:37.649
So what was he doing
dangling by his neck under the bridge?

43:37.753 --> 43:39.317
Percy!

43:39.422 --> 43:42.029
Is that rude? Did I put my foot in it?

43:43.697 --> 43:47.347
No, it's erm... so strange.
It's horrible, you know?

43:47.451 --> 43:50.058
I just...
Everything is just a complete blank.

43:50.267 --> 43:52.561
You know? But as the good doctor said, I...

43:52.665 --> 43:55.898
I was involved in some sort of charity.
I do remember that.

43:56.002 --> 43:57.879
There you go. Plucked.

43:57.984 --> 44:02.259
I mean, what a fool I must have been,
you know, to think that I could have...

44:02.364 --> 44:04.971
you know, changed the world.

44:05.075 --> 44:08.308
That I could have made a difference.
You know, given people hope, eh?

44:09.246 --> 44:13.105
I mean, what an arrogant idiot I must have...

44:13.209 --> 44:15.503
Hey! What's that?
Can I have a look at that?

44:15.607 --> 44:19.257
- What is that you've got?
- It's Beethoven, Ode To Joy.

44:19.362 --> 44:21.760
No, not the song, mate. The pipe.

44:21.864 --> 44:23.846
- Oh...
- I think it belongs to me.

44:24.784 --> 44:26.766
- Really? You think...?
- Yeah.

44:26.870 --> 44:30.520
How do you... how do you know that?
You remembered you're a musician.

44:30.624 --> 44:33.440
Yeah, it's a day of remembering.
Can I please have it back?

44:33.544 --> 44:34.795
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

44:34.900 --> 44:36.360
You're sure this is yours?

44:36.464 --> 44:38.758
- Positive, mate.
- How can you be sure?

44:38.862 --> 44:41.469
I just know these things.
Can I have it back, please?

44:41.574 --> 44:43.346
Yeah. All right, then. Here you go.

44:46.683 --> 44:48.143
- Er...
- Er...

44:48.248 --> 44:49.603
Yeah.

44:49.708 --> 44:50.959
- Yeah...
- All right.

44:51.063 --> 44:53.670
- I don't know where it's gone.
- It's very funny, isn't it?

44:53.775 --> 44:55.756
Can I have my pipe back?
It means a lot to me.

44:55.860 --> 44:57.946
- Yeah, I understand.
- It's a very special pipe.

44:58.050 --> 45:00.970
I don't quite know...
OK, sorry. Got it, got it. Sorry.

45:01.074 --> 45:02.326
There you go. Take it.

45:02.430 --> 45:04.307
- Sorry, sorry.
- Thanks.

45:05.871 --> 45:08.583
Listen, this isn't funny, mate.
That pipe means a lot to me.

45:08.687 --> 45:10.564
- All right?
- It's a little bit funny.

45:10.668 --> 45:13.067
- No, it's not. Get my pipe back.
- All right.

45:13.171 --> 45:15.152
Let me just look around.

45:15.882 --> 45:17.447
What is it doing in a teapot?

45:17.551 --> 45:19.428
That's what I want to know.

45:19.532 --> 45:21.514
- What is it doing in a teapot?
- I don't know.

45:22.348 --> 45:24.329
- Now, thank you very much.
- OK.

45:24.434 --> 45:27.145
- All right. I'm just mucking about.
- All right.

45:27.249 --> 45:29.648
Right! Now you go fetch that thing.

45:29.752 --> 45:31.525
- No, I'm not kidding. Get that thing.
- OK.

45:31.629 --> 45:33.298
- I'm gonna get it.
- Right now.

45:33.402 --> 45:35.592
All right. Just chill out. Just chill out.

45:35.696 --> 45:36.426
There.

45:37.573 --> 45:39.033
Anton. Enough.

45:39.137 --> 45:41.953
I'm sorry. I'm playing around, trying to bond.

45:42.057 --> 45:43.621
Thanks, darling.

45:43.726 --> 45:45.707
Just trying to bond.

45:48.001 --> 45:49.148
OK.

45:49.253 --> 45:51.651
- That was fun!
- Yeah. Funny, funny.

45:54.154 --> 45:56.970
We'll take this one to the back.

45:57.074 --> 45:59.994
I'm worried about Anton.
What's eating him?

46:00.098 --> 46:02.288
He's in love with Valentina.

46:02.392 --> 46:04.269
In love? Who gave him permission?

46:04.478 --> 46:06.564
- It happens.
- The little snake.

46:06.668 --> 46:11.882
Take him from the streets
and that's the thanks I get. I'll skin him alive.

46:11.986 --> 46:14.072
While you're at it, there's the other one.

46:14.176 --> 46:16.157
- The other one?
- The rattlesnake.

46:16.262 --> 46:18.556
- The forgetful cobra.
- Oh, Tony?

46:18.660 --> 46:21.476
- Tony's another kettle of fish.
- Is he?

46:21.580 --> 46:25.230
Yes, he's ambitious, energetic.
A man of destiny.

46:25.334 --> 46:28.463
- And he'll help us win.
- I think he just might.

46:29.506 --> 46:32.947
- Scrumpy sees some good in him.
- She's better off with Anton.

46:33.051 --> 46:34.928
Perhaps I should offer her hand

46:35.033 --> 46:38.265
to whoever helps us win
the next five souls.

46:39.725 --> 46:43.479
That's an even worse idea
than all the other bad ones you've had today.

46:43.584 --> 46:47.546
You're not wrong, you're not wrong.
Neither of them is worthy of her.

46:47.755 --> 46:49.632
You're never wrong, are you?

46:49.736 --> 46:52.865
Percy.
What would I do without you?

46:52.969 --> 46:55.472
- Get a midget.
- What?

46:55.576 --> 46:58.287
You know, short fellow.
A little taller than I am.

46:58.392 --> 47:00.895
Short legs, short feet, big head.
Runs kind of funny.

47:00.999 --> 47:02.876
Yes, I know, I know.

47:05.170 --> 47:09.237
Doctor Parnassus...
as old as the universe itself.

47:09.341 --> 47:11.427
- Versed in...
- Ah, evening, smokers.

47:11.531 --> 47:14.660
Hello, hello, hello.
How's your night tonight? Is it good?

47:14.764 --> 47:17.580
Is it all right? Had a few pints?

47:17.684 --> 47:19.561
- Let the mind...
- Is he OK?

47:19.665 --> 47:21.542
...of the great Dr Parnassus...

47:25.297 --> 47:27.799
What are you doing,
sniffing about like that?

47:27.904 --> 47:31.032
We must concentrate tonight.
Everything depends on it.

47:41.877 --> 47:45.840
Let the great mind... of this doctor...

47:45.944 --> 47:48.656
...transport you...

47:50.011 --> 47:52.410
...to the world of your imagination.

47:53.870 --> 47:57.415
You, my dear,
I see having a very special destiny.

47:57.520 --> 48:00.752
Procrastinate no longer,
you stupid ponce.

48:01.795 --> 48:03.047
Procrastinate no longer.

48:03.151 --> 48:05.549
Oh, no, no, no, a singer.
I bet you have the voice...

48:05.654 --> 48:07.844
- Hi there!
...of an angel.

48:07.948 --> 48:11.493
Don't you, now? Now, come on,
trust me, you're gonna love this experience.

48:11.598 --> 48:13.683
Hey, what are you doing?

48:13.788 --> 48:16.395
Taking you to the heart
of your imagination.

48:16.499 --> 48:18.793
Oh, my God. No way.

48:18.897 --> 48:20.879
Trust me, you will not regret this.

48:20.983 --> 48:22.652
- Go for it, Sal.
- Yeah, go for it, Sal.

48:22.756 --> 48:25.989
- Only if she comes too.
- Now you're talking.

48:26.093 --> 48:29.117
- I can't do two at the same time.
- Are you crazy, kid? Go for it.

48:29.221 --> 48:32.246
- Well, I'm not going on my own.
- We'll do it together.

48:32.350 --> 48:35.061
- Together. Good idea.
- Are you crazy?

48:35.165 --> 48:37.981
Two imaginations in there at the same time?

48:39.545 --> 48:41.631
Oh, no, no, no. Ladies, ladies, ladies.

48:41.735 --> 48:43.508
One at a time's fine, you see.

48:43.612 --> 48:46.949
When there are two, the stronger
imagination will overcome the weaker

48:47.054 --> 48:48.826
and you have no idea what might happen.

48:48.931 --> 48:52.685
- That's really stupid.
- One alone is safe. Follow me.

48:52.789 --> 48:54.666
- Enjoy yourselves.
- Let go!

48:55.292 --> 48:57.795
- Wait, Anton. Anton!
- Have no fear.

48:57.899 --> 48:59.672
Put me down!

48:59.776 --> 49:02.070
She doesn't want to do it on her own.

49:02.175 --> 49:05.407
Your friend is about to have
a life-changing experience.

49:05.512 --> 49:07.284
- Put me down!
- Pillock.

49:07.389 --> 49:08.536
- No!
- What are you doing?

49:08.640 --> 49:11.143
We've got a customer.

49:11.247 --> 49:13.854
Oh, here we go!

49:13.958 --> 49:15.314
Dad. Father.

49:15.836 --> 49:17.191
- Ooh!
- Sal!

49:18.234 --> 49:20.632
Sal! Get off me! Sal!

49:24.282 --> 49:25.534
Dave! Dave!

49:25.638 --> 49:28.245
- Don't shoot the messenger.
- Sal's in there!

49:28.349 --> 49:30.331
Get back! Get back!

49:42.949 --> 49:44.305
Wait. Wait!

49:51.917 --> 49:53.690
Tony!

49:58.800 --> 50:00.677
Come here, you!

50:02.658 --> 50:04.118
Get off!

50:07.977 --> 50:09.854
Come back!

50:11.209 --> 50:12.982
Wa-argh!

50:26.226 --> 50:28.103
Hi there.

50:37.593 --> 50:39.574
Ow!

50:40.304 --> 50:41.555
Shit.

50:41.660 --> 50:43.745
What were you thinking?

50:43.850 --> 50:45.831
Look what you've done.

50:47.499 --> 50:49.689
Jesus.

50:49.794 --> 50:51.566
- Leave us alone.
- I'm trying to help.

50:51.671 --> 50:53.444
Get out of here.

50:53.548 --> 50:55.633
- Leave!
- First to five.

50:55.738 --> 50:57.719
First to five.

50:58.866 --> 51:02.516
- First to five. One down. First to five.
- Ssh. It's OK.

51:02.620 --> 51:04.915
Get up. We've gotta keep moving.

51:05.019 --> 51:08.356
- I know. It's all right. It's fixable.
- Look, all the homeless guys.

51:08.460 --> 51:10.859
- They'll eat our food.
- All right. Let's do this.

51:10.963 --> 51:13.674
- Jesus Christ!
- What are you doing?

51:13.779 --> 51:15.551
- I'm helping.
- You made a mess.

51:15.656 --> 51:17.741
- What? I'm...
- Get out of here. Come on.

51:17.846 --> 51:20.453
- Percy, Percy...
- You're not helping. Get up.

51:20.557 --> 51:23.477
- All right, all right. All right! I'm gone.
- Go away.

51:34.426 --> 51:37.138
Why don't you just claim it all on insurance?

51:37.242 --> 51:40.058
- Bugger off!
- All right. I was just asking.

51:43.603 --> 51:46.106
Oh, God.

51:47.983 --> 51:50.173
That was quite an interesting crowd, wasn't it?

51:50.277 --> 51:52.154
Just leave me alone, mate.

51:53.093 --> 51:57.368
Hey, Val is a little worried about you, mate.

51:57.473 --> 52:01.540
And she wanted me to have a little chat
with you about what happened today,

52:01.644 --> 52:04.877
with the young lady behind the mirror.

52:08.631 --> 52:11.238
Erm... What are you suggesting, mate?

52:13.011 --> 52:15.931
Anton, you can tell me, mate.
We all heard her screaming.

52:16.035 --> 52:18.642
I was screaming as well.

52:18.746 --> 52:20.936
- It was terrifying.
- It was terrifying?

52:21.040 --> 52:23.752
- I don't understand.
- Well, you wouldn't, would you?

52:23.856 --> 52:26.359
You haven't been inside the Doctor's mind,
have you?

52:26.463 --> 52:29.487
- No, I haven't.
- No. Yeah, you, you, my friend,

52:29.592 --> 52:31.573
you probably think it's a scam.

52:31.677 --> 52:33.137
Well, ain't it?

52:33.241 --> 52:35.223
Oh, no.

52:36.474 --> 52:38.560
No, it's not.

52:38.664 --> 52:42.418
I wouldn't, I wouldn't...
I wouldn't expect you to understand.

52:43.044 --> 52:44.817
Not in a million years.

52:44.921 --> 52:48.884
Right, so if Dr Parnassus
can really control people's minds,

52:48.988 --> 52:51.074
then why isn't he ruling the world, then?

52:51.178 --> 52:52.534
Hey?

52:52.638 --> 52:56.288
Why bother with this little... sideshow act?

52:56.392 --> 52:59.208
It's not a sideshow.
He don't wanna rule the world.

53:01.710 --> 53:04.630
He wants the world to rule itself.

53:06.612 --> 53:07.863
Yeah.

53:09.427 --> 53:12.034
And what about the mirror? What's that about?

53:12.139 --> 53:14.120
- A bit of hocus-pocus?
- No, mate.

53:14.224 --> 53:16.727
Tony, Tony, Tony, you don't get it, man.

53:18.813 --> 53:20.690
It is...

53:21.628 --> 53:24.757
It's impossible to describe. It's just a mystery.

53:24.861 --> 53:26.217
Yeah.

53:26.321 --> 53:30.492
It's everything. It's you, it's me, it's us.
He holds the universe behind that mirror.

53:30.597 --> 53:33.099
Does "first to five" mean anything to you?

53:38.626 --> 53:40.816
I thought you were supposed to be
the clever one.

53:41.963 --> 53:44.049
It's all over. It's lost.

53:44.779 --> 53:47.803
- Finished. Over.
- Ssh. Don't say that.

53:47.907 --> 53:49.576
It's never over.

53:49.680 --> 53:52.704
You're supposed to be immortal,
remember?

53:53.434 --> 53:55.416
Honestly, it's gonna be OK, Dad.

53:55.520 --> 53:57.501
How can you understand?

53:57.606 --> 53:59.066
Hm?

53:59.170 --> 54:01.151
You're a child.

54:01.256 --> 54:03.133
You've never loved.

54:04.384 --> 54:06.261
Not like I have.

54:08.138 --> 54:10.224
From the moment I looked up...

54:10.954 --> 54:14.291
<i>...and saw her, I was captivated.</i>

54:15.542 --> 54:16.898
<i>A prisoner for life.</i>

54:29.307 --> 54:31.184
<i>I was a thousand years old.</i>

54:32.540 --> 54:34.417
<i>How could I woo her?</i>

54:35.356 --> 54:38.276
<i>How could I ever make her mine?</i>

54:40.153 --> 54:43.698
Percy, you devil!
Let go. You don't understand.

54:43.803 --> 54:45.784
- Don't be a fool.
- Let go.

54:45.888 --> 54:48.495
- You can't die. You're immortal.
- Let go!

54:48.600 --> 54:51.728
You'll just end up broken in an eternity ward.

54:51.832 --> 54:54.127
And I'll end up looking after you...

54:54.231 --> 54:56.525
- Just let go, you little shit.
...forever!

54:59.236 --> 55:01.113
No!

55:03.199 --> 55:07.370
<i>And at times like these,
the Devil was never far away.</i>

55:10.186 --> 55:12.376
Why look so glum, Parny?

55:13.523 --> 55:15.817
Accentuate the positive.

55:16.651 --> 55:20.301
<i>He granted me mortality again...</i>

55:20.406 --> 55:22.700
<i>and youth and new powers.</i>

55:22.804 --> 55:24.785
<i>Greater powers.</i>

55:25.828 --> 55:27.601
<i>And I won her.</i>

55:27.705 --> 55:29.687
<i>I was so in love.</i>

55:30.417 --> 55:32.398
<i>So in love.</i>

55:36.048 --> 55:38.029
<i>But at what price?</i>

55:39.176 --> 55:41.158
<i>What price?</i>

55:45.955 --> 55:47.936
What's up, Doc?

55:51.795 --> 55:53.776
But at what price?

55:53.880 --> 55:55.757
But at what price?

56:06.081 --> 56:08.271
Pick up those rotten apples.

56:09.210 --> 56:11.191
Percy, pick up those rotten apples.

56:11.295 --> 56:13.277
- Ow.
- Sorry.

56:14.319 --> 56:16.405
Thank God it's only cuts and bruises.

56:16.509 --> 56:18.491
- Yeah.
- I thought we'd lost you.

56:18.595 --> 56:20.159
Oh, sweetheart.

56:20.264 --> 56:22.245
What a sweet thing to say.

56:22.349 --> 56:24.226
Oh, look at you.

56:24.331 --> 56:26.416
I've been meaning to ask you
about your father.

56:26.520 --> 56:28.919
He seems to be in a terrible state, you know.

56:29.023 --> 56:31.526
Now, is it a financial thing? Is it money?

56:31.630 --> 56:32.777
I don't know.

56:32.882 --> 56:35.802
Because if it is,
you know I can help out in that area.

56:35.906 --> 56:38.826
- I don't know.
- Or is it the show, perhaps?

56:38.930 --> 56:41.224
I don't care about the show any more.

56:41.329 --> 56:43.206
Or what about the police? Maybe...

56:43.310 --> 56:46.021
Bring on the police. I'm sick of living like this.

56:46.125 --> 56:48.211
Oh, really?

56:48.315 --> 56:52.487
Oh, aren't you a little toughie, eh?

56:52.591 --> 56:54.885
Now, listen, you shouldn't be talking this way.

56:54.989 --> 56:58.848
All right? It's very important
what you're doing. It's family stuff. You know?

56:59.056 --> 57:03.749
Maybe it's just things ought to be done
a little different around here.

57:03.853 --> 57:06.148
What different sort of way do you suggest?

57:06.252 --> 57:08.338
Morning. How was your sleep last night?

57:08.442 --> 57:10.423
You had a nasty bump on your head.

57:10.527 --> 57:12.717
Different? What do you mean?

57:12.822 --> 57:17.514
Well, I've been thinking, sir, that, you know,
it's quite obvious that people...

57:17.619 --> 57:20.121
you know,
not many people are attracted to the show.

57:20.226 --> 57:21.894
Oh, thank you so much.

57:21.999 --> 57:25.648
Well, forgive me, but I have
a couple of solutions to your problem.

57:25.753 --> 57:30.028
I was thinking of changing
the style of the show.

57:30.133 --> 57:34.721
I would change the audience, perhaps.

57:34.825 --> 57:36.598
- Change?
- Yeah.

57:36.702 --> 57:40.039
But in my opinion I'd change both.
You know, that's just me.

57:40.144 --> 57:41.916
- And I'd...
- Change the show?

57:42.021 --> 57:44.523
Who the friggin' hell do you think you are?

57:44.628 --> 57:47.235
Don't be so afraid of change, mate.

57:47.339 --> 57:51.927
The fact of the matter is,
this show, the stage, it's just not...

57:53.075 --> 57:56.099
I don't know what the word is.
It's... But you know, it's not...

57:56.203 --> 57:57.246
Modern?

57:57.350 --> 57:59.019
Modern. Yes.

58:00.166 --> 58:04.024
You see, people want modern.
They want, you know, like... like this.

58:04.128 --> 58:07.153
See. This here is contemporary.
This is what people want.

58:07.257 --> 58:08.821
I know this world. Trust me. All right?

58:08.925 --> 58:11.741
Now, with you and your
mind control thingamajigamy,

58:11.845 --> 58:13.722
we need to meet the public halfway.

58:13.827 --> 58:16.747
You know?
The right public in the right part of town.

58:16.851 --> 58:18.624
- What about the filth?
- What?

58:18.728 --> 58:20.709
- The filth.
- He means the police.

58:20.814 --> 58:23.629
Oh, well, there'll be a better class of filth too.

58:23.733 --> 58:25.611
- That will be the day.
- Yeah. Listen.

58:25.715 --> 58:29.365
The secret is, you know, not to hide.

58:29.469 --> 58:31.346
Be bold. Be colourful.

58:31.450 --> 58:35.934
You know, or actually, you know,
be less colourful, perhaps.

58:36.039 --> 58:39.689
And go places people would
never expect you to be at.

58:39.793 --> 58:42.087
You know? Think.

58:42.921 --> 58:44.903
Sir, you saved my life.

58:45.841 --> 58:48.344
Now let me do something in return for you.

58:49.178 --> 58:50.534
Please.

58:51.681 --> 58:53.662
Would you hold on to that?

58:53.767 --> 58:55.748
Scrumpy.

59:00.754 --> 59:04.195
- You believe in coincidence?
- No, there's no such thing.

59:04.299 --> 59:06.281
Isn't that what you always told me?

59:06.385 --> 59:09.200
- Everything has a reason.
- Yes, that's what I believe.

59:09.305 --> 59:11.390
And the cards. Do you believe in them?

