01:20:29.661 --> 01:20:32.478
God, you've no idea what it's like to feel,
I mean, like a god.

01:20:32.581 --> 01:20:34.563
My lungs were full of air.

01:20:35.398 --> 01:20:39.153
Who were they? Who were those big
Russian men with the fists in my face?

01:20:39.256 --> 01:20:40.821
- That's not important.
- It is.

01:20:40.924 --> 01:20:43.740
- Getting back to that... full body...
- You stole their money.

01:20:43.845 --> 01:20:46.556
- No, I didn't.
- You stole their money.

01:20:46.661 --> 01:20:48.850
That's what I heard them say,
with my own ears.

01:20:48.954 --> 01:20:51.144
- You're going to believe them, not me?
- I might.

01:20:51.249 --> 01:20:53.857
And what are these?
Explain these marks on your forehead.

01:20:53.961 --> 01:20:56.359
I don't know. Something satanic... Devil...

01:20:56.464 --> 01:20:58.966
Listen, those were irredeemably bad men.

01:20:59.070 --> 01:21:00.948
Hm?

01:21:01.052 --> 01:21:03.034
OK? And I'm essentially good.

01:21:05.432 --> 01:21:08.769
Oh, sorry, Tony's trying to be, what,

01:21:09.499 --> 01:21:10.750
- prim?
- Self-righteous.

01:21:10.855 --> 01:21:12.628
- Self-righteous?
- Yes.

01:21:12.731 --> 01:21:14.609
- Well, you want me to be honest?
- Oh, yeah.

01:21:14.713 --> 01:21:16.277
- You want the truth?
- I'd love it.

01:21:16.381 --> 01:21:18.051
- Really?
- Think you can muster it up?

01:21:18.154 --> 01:21:21.075
Do you think you can
get it out of that carcass of yours?

01:21:21.179 --> 01:21:23.577
Just for once. Just for me.

01:21:23.682 --> 01:21:25.350
Eh?

01:21:25.454 --> 01:21:27.853
When I set up my charity, Anton -

01:21:27.958 --> 01:21:29.835
a charity for kids -

01:21:30.877 --> 01:21:35.154
I needed money,
and I accepted a loan from those men.

01:21:40.158 --> 01:21:42.036
I had no id...

01:21:42.140 --> 01:21:44.539
I didn't know.

01:21:44.644 --> 01:21:47.354
They laundered dirty money
through the charity.

01:21:51.944 --> 01:21:53.925
I know I was stupid.

01:21:54.654 --> 01:21:56.636
I made a mistake...

01:21:57.574 --> 01:22:00.286
...and the kids weren't to blame.

01:22:01.538 --> 01:22:03.728
They were the innocents.

01:22:03.832 --> 01:22:05.709
But I...

01:22:05.814 --> 01:22:08.316
I carry that every day.

01:22:08.420 --> 01:22:10.402
Every day of my life.

01:22:15.304 --> 01:22:17.286
All right.

01:22:18.223 --> 01:22:20.831
- You wanted the truth.
- Sorry.

01:22:25.628 --> 01:22:27.609
Are you OK?

01:22:28.548 --> 01:22:30.529
Thank you for that.

01:22:31.050 --> 01:22:33.137
Where are the ladders?

01:22:33.241 --> 01:22:35.118
Will you show me?

01:22:35.952 --> 01:22:37.933
The clouds...

01:22:38.977 --> 01:22:40.541
Nah.

01:22:43.669 --> 01:22:45.129
Anton...

01:22:45.234 --> 01:22:47.111
Hey, mate, don't leave...

01:22:47.214 --> 01:22:49.196
- Ow, ow, ow.
- Don't leave me here.

01:22:49.301 --> 01:22:50.657
Anton!

01:22:50.761 --> 01:22:51.908
Don't leave me. Come on.

01:22:52.011 --> 01:22:53.993
I almost died today.

01:22:55.558 --> 01:22:57.748
Don't leave me. Mate, come on.

01:22:57.852 --> 01:22:58.895
I ju...

01:22:58.999 --> 01:23:00.251
Oh, this...

01:23:00.356 --> 01:23:02.337
I needed the money!

01:23:02.441 --> 01:23:06.507
When you run a charity,
you have to give lots of money away.

01:23:06.612 --> 01:23:08.177
The red tape, the bureauc...

01:23:08.280 --> 01:23:12.139
You have no idea what a bunch of fascists
the Charity Commission is.

01:23:12.661 --> 01:23:15.268
How many more times
does he have to say sorry?

01:23:15.371 --> 01:23:19.126
This is ridiculous. Bring him down.

01:23:19.230 --> 01:23:20.794
Listen, Valentina. Look at me.

01:23:20.899 --> 01:23:25.384
Why can't you see that he has betrayed us
and he has fooled us all? It's so obvious.

01:23:25.487 --> 01:23:27.990
- Open the hatch!
- You're just jealous.

01:23:28.094 --> 01:23:30.493
It's not funny.

01:23:30.598 --> 01:23:32.580
I'm not jealous. I'm not jealous.

01:23:32.683 --> 01:23:34.039
Percy, open the hatch.

01:23:34.143 --> 01:23:37.898
Why would he wanna come down?
He knows we don't like him.

01:23:38.003 --> 01:23:40.609
Come on, you guys. Look at this stuff.

01:23:42.174 --> 01:23:43.947
Have you forgotten how it was before he came?

01:23:44.052 --> 01:23:46.031
No, no, I haven't forgotten, Valentina.

01:23:46.136 --> 01:23:48.847
It was so pure.
Will you please just unzip me here?

01:23:48.952 --> 01:23:50.620
Pure?

01:23:51.663 --> 01:23:54.062
And the women?
You saw their faces when they came out.

01:23:54.167 --> 01:23:55.835
I saw his faces, Valentina.

01:23:55.940 --> 01:23:58.442
I saw both of his faces.
He has at least two. If not more.

01:23:58.547 --> 01:24:01.989
It's my birthday.
Percy, we're supposed to be celebrating.

01:24:04.282 --> 01:24:05.846
At least Tony remembered.

01:24:06.576 --> 01:24:08.662
Would you please listen to me
for one second?

01:24:13.042 --> 01:24:14.503
No.

01:24:14.606 --> 01:24:16.379
Leave it.

01:24:22.115 --> 01:24:24.514
Let him in, it's... Tony?

01:24:24.618 --> 01:24:26.494
No, I think not.

01:24:28.581 --> 01:24:30.458
Sit down.

01:24:39.636 --> 01:24:41.825
Can somebody please answer the door?

01:24:41.930 --> 01:24:44.432
I can't stand not answering the door,
or the telephone.

01:24:44.536 --> 01:24:47.039
Drives me crazy. It's not in my nature.

01:24:47.144 --> 01:24:48.812
I won't be able to sleep.

01:24:48.917 --> 01:24:52.462
The knock-knock-knocking
is gonna be in my head all night.

01:24:52.567 --> 01:24:53.923
Just things like that.

01:25:07.479 --> 01:25:08.419
Well...

01:25:10.087 --> 01:25:11.234
...you've won.

01:25:12.172 --> 01:25:13.632
It's over.

01:25:13.737 --> 01:25:17.178
- Four rotten Russkies?
- And the girl from the pub.

01:25:17.283 --> 01:25:19.472
Ahh, Sal.

01:25:21.559 --> 01:25:23.852
She don't count. Do you, Sal?

01:25:23.957 --> 01:25:26.459
And that's how you take your pleasure,
is it?

01:25:26.564 --> 01:25:28.336
Toying with me?

01:25:28.441 --> 01:25:30.005
Like a cat with a mouse?

01:25:30.109 --> 01:25:33.238
Come on.
Sal didn't get to make a real choice.

01:25:33.342 --> 01:25:36.262
You were out for the count.
It wouldn't be fair.

01:25:36.366 --> 01:25:39.912
You got four...
So, you know, you get your friend Tony.

01:25:40.643 --> 01:25:42.206
Come on.

01:25:43.041 --> 01:25:44.396
We're even.

01:25:45.127 --> 01:25:47.108
It's not quite over.

01:25:49.611 --> 01:25:51.279
Not quite.

01:25:52.323 --> 01:25:53.991
Ho-ho, look at the time.

01:25:54.095 --> 01:25:55.973
It's almost eleven.

01:26:04.420 --> 01:26:05.357
Dad?

01:26:05.462 --> 01:26:06.922
What?

01:26:07.027 --> 01:26:11.511
Oh. We're going to have to give
another performance.

01:26:11.615 --> 01:26:13.388
Now, quickly.

01:26:13.493 --> 01:26:14.847
Er...

01:26:15.787 --> 01:26:17.768
Get ready to move out.

01:26:17.871 --> 01:26:20.062
- Who was that?
- Just somebody asking the way.

01:26:20.167 --> 01:26:22.357
I overheard you. He wasn't asking the way.

01:26:22.461 --> 01:26:24.547
Yes. Tony! Percy!

01:26:24.651 --> 01:26:27.571
- What's going on?
- Not now, Scrumpy, not now.

01:26:27.675 --> 01:26:30.490
- Where's Tony?
- What are you hiding?

01:26:30.595 --> 01:26:35.288
It's to do with that rambling story
you started telling and never finished.

01:26:35.392 --> 01:26:36.748
What are you hiding?

01:26:36.853 --> 01:26:38.104
Oh, you...

01:26:41.545 --> 01:26:43.527
I want to know the truth.

01:26:47.280 --> 01:26:49.262
The truth?

01:26:52.703 --> 01:26:54.476
I am thousands of years old.

01:26:55.416 --> 01:26:57.605
I have been immortal.

01:26:58.440 --> 01:27:00.108
And...

01:27:00.942 --> 01:27:02.924
...I did make a bargain with the Devil.

01:27:04.175 --> 01:27:06.053
For that woman, in the story?

01:27:06.157 --> 01:27:07.616
Yes.

01:27:10.120 --> 01:27:11.893
Your mother.

01:27:17.628 --> 01:27:22.426
I regained my youth and I won her.

01:27:22.529 --> 01:27:24.302
We lived in joy.

01:27:25.032 --> 01:27:27.223
We grew old together.

01:27:27.326 --> 01:27:30.350
And then one day
she came and told me that she was pregnant.

01:27:30.455 --> 01:27:32.541
Imagine.

01:27:32.645 --> 01:27:35.253
60 years old and pregnant.

01:27:35.357 --> 01:27:37.234
It was a miracle.

01:27:38.277 --> 01:27:40.466
But she died giving birth.

01:27:43.595 --> 01:27:44.846
Me?

01:27:44.951 --> 01:27:46.515
Yes.

01:27:48.809 --> 01:27:51.417
Miracle or a mistake?

01:27:51.521 --> 01:27:53.710
You're the best mistake I ever made.

01:27:55.067 --> 01:27:57.465
And the bargain with the Devil?

01:27:58.300 --> 01:28:00.176
There are two parts to a bargain.

01:28:00.281 --> 01:28:02.054
He granted me mortality

01:28:02.158 --> 01:28:09.667
on condition that any child I would father...
would, at the age of 16, belong to him.

01:28:12.065 --> 01:28:13.734
No.

01:28:13.838 --> 01:28:15.819
You're just telling a story.

01:28:16.654 --> 01:28:18.948
A cruel story.

01:28:19.052 --> 01:28:21.451
- Why should I believe it?
- Because it's true.

01:28:21.556 --> 01:28:24.475
Every word of it's true.
But... But there's a new wager.

01:28:24.580 --> 01:28:27.605
All is not lost. Now, we can win, we can win.

01:28:27.708 --> 01:28:29.585
- You'll be mine again.
- Enough, enough!

01:28:29.689 --> 01:28:31.255
- Stop!
- No, listen to me, Scrumpy.

01:28:31.358 --> 01:28:33.131
Listen to yourself!

01:28:33.965 --> 01:28:36.886
Who are you? I don't know any more!

01:28:36.989 --> 01:28:40.014
All my life you've filled my head with dreams.

01:28:40.119 --> 01:28:41.891
Your dreams.

01:28:41.996 --> 01:28:44.185
You're making deals with the Devil.

01:28:45.019 --> 01:28:47.105
What am I?

01:28:47.210 --> 01:28:49.816
A pathetic bet?

01:28:49.920 --> 01:28:51.902
Another mistake?

01:28:53.675 --> 01:28:55.969
- Val!
- Oh, she's gone.

01:28:57.325 --> 01:28:59.829
- She's gone.
- Telling the truth...

01:29:00.662 --> 01:29:02.539
Always a bad idea.

01:29:02.644 --> 01:29:06.920
Oh, hold your tongue, you smug little pustule!

01:29:07.024 --> 01:29:09.319
Get out of my sight and stay out!

01:29:18.287 --> 01:29:22.042
Perhaps you'll find a midget -
if you're lucky.

01:29:26.734 --> 01:29:28.402
Valentina!

01:29:31.844 --> 01:29:33.616
Valentina!

01:29:37.997 --> 01:29:39.665
Valentina!

01:29:42.063 --> 01:29:43.733
Valentina!

01:29:47.070 --> 01:29:48.947
Fuck.

01:29:51.449 --> 01:29:53.118
Come on.

01:29:57.811 --> 01:30:01.357
- What are you doing?
- Trying to save your daughter's life, sir.

01:30:01.462 --> 01:30:02.816
Save?

01:30:02.921 --> 01:30:04.172
How?

01:30:04.277 --> 01:30:06.675
Well, I figured I could be the fifth soul.

01:30:06.780 --> 01:30:09.282
See. I could take that risk, sir.

01:30:09.387 --> 01:30:11.994
You're a good lad, Tony, but it's no use.

01:30:12.098 --> 01:30:13.559
We still have time, don't we?

01:30:13.662 --> 01:30:15.644
Yes, of course there's still time, but...

01:30:15.748 --> 01:30:18.982
You know I'd never ask for anything in return?
It's not in my nature.

01:30:19.085 --> 01:30:23.674
Well, you're a saint, my boy, you're a saint,
but it... it's positively useless.

01:30:23.777 --> 01:30:25.550
Actually, there is one thing.

01:30:25.655 --> 01:30:26.802
Um...

01:30:26.907 --> 01:30:31.391
How about an initiation
into the secrets of the trance?

01:30:31.496 --> 01:30:33.581
- Oh, I can't do that, no.
- What? Why not?

01:30:33.686 --> 01:30:35.458
- No, it won't work.
- I could do it.

01:30:35.563 --> 01:30:37.544
- You'd be a great teacher.
- It hurts my head.

01:30:37.648 --> 01:30:39.526
- What do you mean?
- Too up... Too upset.

01:30:39.630 --> 01:30:42.863
Oh, it's not a time to be upset, sir.
It's time to be happy.

01:30:42.967 --> 01:30:44.636
I mean, think about Valentina.

01:30:44.739 --> 01:30:47.346
Now, we need you to be in a trance
for this to work.

01:30:47.451 --> 01:30:48.808
- Mm.
- Can you give me that?

01:30:48.910 --> 01:30:50.997
- Well...
- Come on. Close your eyes, come on.

01:30:52.769 --> 01:30:55.377
Close your eyes. Think of the ocean.

01:30:55.481 --> 01:30:58.297
The ocean going in and out.

01:30:58.401 --> 01:31:01.217
In and... out.

01:31:01.322 --> 01:31:04.346
Yes, in and... out.

01:31:05.805 --> 01:31:08.725
In and out.

01:31:10.811 --> 01:31:13.001
And in and out.

01:31:20.718 --> 01:31:22.178
Shit!

01:31:23.534 --> 01:31:25.933
I don't have time for this.
Pull yourself together.

01:31:26.036 --> 01:31:27.601
This is not a time to be playing baby.

01:31:27.706 --> 01:31:28.957
- It's no good.
- What isn't?

01:31:29.061 --> 01:31:30.105
It's no good.

01:31:30.208 --> 01:31:31.981
- Now concentrate.
- Won't work.

01:31:32.086 --> 01:31:34.588
Damn it, Tony, just... I need to calm down.

01:31:34.692 --> 01:31:36.256
You need to calm down.

01:31:36.361 --> 01:31:42.410
You just need to relax
and try and um... think of... chocolate.

01:31:42.514 --> 01:31:45.643
Um, melting away on a hot stove.

01:31:45.746 --> 01:31:48.562
It's just melting, melting...

01:31:55.028 --> 01:31:56.592
Good, good, good, good, good.

01:31:56.697 --> 01:31:58.991
Right, stay with me, sir. Stay with me.

01:32:00.973 --> 01:32:03.371
- Oi, what's wrong with you?
- Duty!

01:32:03.475 --> 01:32:05.456
Truth!

01:32:05.561 --> 01:32:06.707
- Oi.
- Justice!

01:32:06.812 --> 01:32:09.003
- Now, what is your problem?
- It's lies.

01:32:09.106 --> 01:32:11.193
Just listen. All right now, calm down.

01:32:11.297 --> 01:32:13.175
Bloody hell, father like daughter.

01:32:13.278 --> 01:32:15.051
- Now come here, look at me.
- No.

01:32:15.155 --> 01:32:16.720
- Calm down.
- No, no.

01:32:16.825 --> 01:32:18.596
- What is wrong? Talk to me.
- Lying...

01:32:18.701 --> 01:32:21.620
- Who's lying?
- I used to think it was precious. It's not.

01:32:21.725 --> 01:32:24.749
What, the lmaginarium?
What are you talking about?

01:32:24.854 --> 01:32:28.088
- I can't even run away.
- You can't even run away from what?

01:32:28.192 --> 01:32:29.860
- You wanna run away from this?
- Yes.

01:32:29.965 --> 01:32:33.301
Listen, if you wanna get away,
I can take you to a beautiful place.

01:32:33.406 --> 01:32:35.699
All right? I can take you somewhere.

01:32:35.804 --> 01:32:39.350
I can get you out of this darkness.
I'll take you to the light, all right?

01:32:39.454 --> 01:32:41.227
I'll take you somewhere beautiful.

01:32:41.331 --> 01:32:43.938
Just you and me. Now trust me.
Come with me now.

01:32:44.043 --> 01:32:46.025
We don't have time for this. All right?

01:32:46.129 --> 01:32:48.214
Now, it's gonna be a paradise, all right?

01:32:48.318 --> 01:32:50.717
It's my world. It could be our world.

01:32:50.821 --> 01:32:52.594
Trust me, it'll be perfect.

01:32:53.949 --> 01:32:56.661
Ah, now. No, see, yeah, that's bad.

01:32:56.766 --> 01:32:59.476
- Did some light reading and found this.
- Can I have a look?

01:32:59.581 --> 01:33:02.084
- Valentina might be interested.
- We don't have time.

01:33:02.189 --> 01:33:04.170
- We gotta get inside.
- He's a liar!

01:33:04.274 --> 01:33:06.881
- He's nothing but a liar, Val.
- This was in the past.

01:33:06.986 --> 01:33:09.176
In the present, I have to get you in there.

01:33:09.280 --> 01:33:11.470
- So come here and trust me...
- Shut up!

01:33:12.721 --> 01:33:14.389
Shut up!

01:33:15.120 --> 01:33:16.788
Val! Valentina!

01:33:16.893 --> 01:33:18.249
No!

01:33:19.500 --> 01:33:21.585
- Aarghh!
- Right.

01:33:22.836 --> 01:33:24.923
I didn't want it to get to this point, mate.

01:33:25.652 --> 01:33:28.781
You don't believe what you read
in the newspapers.

01:33:30.241 --> 01:33:31.597
Especially The Mirror.

01:33:43.381 --> 01:33:45.467
You were right.

01:33:45.571 --> 01:33:47.449
The world is beautiful.

01:33:48.386 --> 01:33:52.036
- Hmm.
- I always dreamed you'd be like this.

01:33:52.141 --> 01:33:54.123
Yeah?

01:33:59.441 --> 01:34:03.300
And er... well, didn't I say you'd be happy here?

01:34:04.238 --> 01:34:06.846
Isn't it just... perfect?

01:34:06.949 --> 01:34:08.305
Perfect.

01:34:09.765 --> 01:34:10.913
Hmm.

01:34:11.018 --> 01:34:13.207
If only we didn't have to make a choice.

01:34:13.311 --> 01:34:15.396
There doesn't have to be a choice.

01:34:15.501 --> 01:34:18.109
Sweetheart, a rule's a rule.

01:34:18.213 --> 01:34:19.777
Those are my father's rules.

01:34:19.882 --> 01:34:21.445
We're free.

01:34:22.280 --> 01:34:24.157
- See?
- Oh.

01:34:24.260 --> 01:34:25.722
- Really?
- Really.

01:34:25.825 --> 01:34:27.494
Hmm.

01:34:27.598 --> 01:34:29.475
Well, er... I suppose you are right.

01:34:30.309 --> 01:34:33.960
Tony, we're free if we want to be.

01:34:35.106 --> 01:34:37.193
Let's just let the river do the choosing.

01:34:38.548 --> 01:34:40.843
Now... kiss me.

01:34:52.940 --> 01:34:55.651
Oh, Val, you're a very naughty girl.

01:35:00.865 --> 01:35:03.473
