01:35:03.578 --> 01:35:05.871
âª Like a big pizza pie

01:35:05.976 --> 01:35:08.270
âª That's amore

01:35:08.374 --> 01:35:11.085
âª When the stars make you drool

01:35:11.189 --> 01:35:13.484
âª Just like pasta fazool

01:35:13.588 --> 01:35:15.257
âª You're in love

01:35:18.385 --> 01:35:20.367
You know...

01:35:21.931 --> 01:35:23.599
...I think maybe I love you, Tony.

01:35:24.539 --> 01:35:26.521
Val.

01:35:26.624 --> 01:35:29.022
We should lie here more often.

01:35:30.899 --> 01:35:32.986
Get married.

01:35:33.715 --> 01:35:36.114
Make babies.

01:35:43.622 --> 01:35:46.960
- Well, maybe this is my, er... choice.
- What d'you mean?

01:35:47.064 --> 01:35:49.671
That's a child. It's not a choice.

01:35:49.776 --> 01:35:51.549
- She needs our help.
- Yes.

01:35:51.652 --> 01:35:54.468
It's OK. It's OK.
Come here, we'll help you.

01:35:54.573 --> 01:35:56.658
Look, don't worry. Don't worry, come here.

01:35:56.763 --> 01:35:58.745
No, no, it's OK, we're here to help you.

01:35:58.848 --> 01:36:00.517
- Tony, help me. She's strong.
- No!

01:36:00.622 --> 01:36:03.229
Come, it's OK. Honestly, no.

01:36:03.332 --> 01:36:05.419
No, we're friends. Come here.

01:36:07.921 --> 01:36:10.529
Huh?

01:36:11.571 --> 01:36:14.178
- Smile for the cameras, sweetheart.
- Lovely!

01:36:14.283 --> 01:36:16.368
I think this is my world.

01:36:16.473 --> 01:36:18.036
âª Ode To Joy

01:36:19.498 --> 01:36:22.834
Well, sustainability's great.
I mean, if you can achieve it.

01:36:22.939 --> 01:36:25.650
The problem in most cases
is you simply can't get there.

01:36:25.755 --> 01:36:30.134
Don't you risk entrenching the need for charity
by institutionalising it?

01:36:30.239 --> 01:36:33.680
It's an unfortunate truism that charity,
like poor little Olga here,

01:36:33.785 --> 01:36:35.766
is always with us, to coin a phrase.

01:36:35.870 --> 01:36:37.851
Ah, there you are, my darling.

01:36:37.955 --> 01:36:41.501
Ladies and gentlemen, isn't she a wonder?
Hello. Big smiles.

01:36:41.605 --> 01:36:45.046
- What's your message to the President?
- I wouldn't presume to have one.

01:36:45.151 --> 01:36:49.115
I think, luckily for the Foundation,
we see eye-to-eye on most things.

01:36:49.218 --> 01:36:51.409
- Tony, I had something...
- Oh, one sec, love.

01:36:55.372 --> 01:36:57.145
Mr President, thank you for coming.

01:36:57.249 --> 01:36:59.126
- There he is.
- It's great to see you.

01:36:59.231 --> 01:37:03.088
âª We are the children of the world

01:37:03.193 --> 01:37:06.843
âª And we have suffered for your sins

01:37:07.469 --> 01:37:10.597
âª But if you open up your heart

01:37:10.701 --> 01:37:13.726
âª A beautiful new day begins...

01:37:14.560 --> 01:37:18.418
Ladies and gentlemen,
please be upstanding for the President.

01:37:19.774 --> 01:37:21.756
Yes, so many suffering children.

01:37:21.860 --> 01:37:26.032
So much opportunity to do some good, really.
It'll be a big year for our Foundation.

01:37:26.136 --> 01:37:28.951
President is getting ready to make a speech,
introduce me.

01:37:29.056 --> 01:37:30.933
- Yeah.
- Lovely.

01:37:31.037 --> 01:37:32.914
Talk to you tomorrow. Yes, absolutely.

01:37:33.019 --> 01:37:35.209
I've only three words to say.

01:37:36.773 --> 01:37:39.068
Well done, Tony.

01:37:39.171 --> 01:37:41.570
Ah, the children. The children.

01:37:43.029 --> 01:37:45.637
This is a vital moment
for the future of the Foundation.

01:37:45.742 --> 01:37:48.452
- Children of the world depend on us.
- Valentina!

01:37:51.790 --> 01:37:53.564
Valentina!

01:37:53.667 --> 01:37:55.336
- Anton?
- Yep.

01:37:56.796 --> 01:37:59.403
- Anton?
- Yes, yes, listen to me right now.

01:37:59.507 --> 01:38:01.488
This is nothing to do with you. This is him.

01:38:01.593 --> 01:38:03.574
- Where are you?
- This is his imagination.

01:38:03.679 --> 01:38:04.930
Right, call security now!

01:38:05.035 --> 01:38:06.911
Down here, under your arm. Yes, yes.

01:38:07.015 --> 01:38:09.414
- What... Anton, what are you doing here?
- Look.

01:38:09.519 --> 01:38:13.064
"Disgraced Director of children's
charity, Suffer The Little Children..."

01:38:13.169 --> 01:38:15.254
He's lying. It's not right, he's jeal...

01:38:15.358 --> 01:38:19.739
"...was arrested last week on charges
of stealing organs of Third World children

01:38:19.843 --> 01:38:22.138
and selling them to wealthy Westerners."

01:38:23.701 --> 01:38:25.579
- Come back.
- What are you doing?

01:38:25.683 --> 01:38:27.143
- That's Anton.
- He's lying.

01:38:27.247 --> 01:38:29.229
- Stop!
- Whose side are you on?

01:38:31.420 --> 01:38:33.296
You, you've betrayed me, haven't you?

01:38:33.399 --> 01:38:36.633
- After all we've been through.
- Don't you touch her!

01:38:36.738 --> 01:38:41.012
I'll show 'em! I'll show them all, Tony.
I'll show 'em all.

01:38:41.117 --> 01:38:43.725
Have had the courage
to fight poverty...

01:38:43.829 --> 01:38:46.644
- He's a liar, he's a fraud!
- Come here, you little bastard!

01:38:46.749 --> 01:38:48.522
- Do not believe him.
- I'll kill you.

01:38:48.626 --> 01:38:51.441
...passion... and dedication...
- All right, all right...

01:38:51.546 --> 01:38:53.631
- Trying to...
...careers and struggles...

01:38:53.735 --> 01:38:56.134
Shut up! Trying to ruin my world!

01:38:56.239 --> 01:38:58.012
Stop him!

01:38:58.116 --> 01:39:00.306
- My God.
- Somebody stop him.

01:39:00.411 --> 01:39:02.599
- He's a monster!
- Stop him!

01:39:02.704 --> 01:39:04.895
He was being a very naughty little boy.

01:39:08.544 --> 01:39:10.421
Christ. Mr President.

01:39:10.526 --> 01:39:11.986
Fuck.

01:39:12.091 --> 01:39:13.445
Right.

01:39:14.280 --> 01:39:15.427
Stop him!

01:39:15.532 --> 01:39:17.722
Get out of me way! Christ.

01:39:19.599 --> 01:39:21.476
Er, exit sign?

01:39:21.581 --> 01:39:23.040
Er, oh, no.

01:39:23.144 --> 01:39:25.334
No! No!

01:39:25.439 --> 01:39:27.421
No! I can't. No, no, no...

01:39:28.776 --> 01:39:30.654
No, not good. Er...

01:39:31.800 --> 01:39:34.303
I'm coming after you, Tony!
I'm coming after you!

01:39:34.407 --> 01:39:35.972
No, get off me.

01:39:36.076 --> 01:39:37.640
Get off of me.

01:39:45.462 --> 01:39:47.131
Anton! Anton!

01:39:47.235 --> 01:39:48.694
- Are you OK?
- Are you all right?

01:39:48.799 --> 01:39:50.572
Val! Val, watch out!

01:39:50.676 --> 01:39:52.240
Be careful. Are you all right?

01:39:52.344 --> 01:39:54.117
Valentina.

01:39:54.222 --> 01:39:55.995
- Val. Val!
- Anton.

01:39:58.810 --> 01:39:59.957
Anton.

01:40:01.417 --> 01:40:03.607
Val, help me.

01:40:03.711 --> 01:40:05.588
Hold on to me. Hold on to me, please.

01:40:05.693 --> 01:40:07.675
Hold on!

01:40:08.404 --> 01:40:11.533
Aaarrghh! Ohh! Ohh!

01:40:12.576 --> 01:40:13.932
I'm sorry.

01:40:14.036 --> 01:40:15.600
I was so wrong.

01:40:15.704 --> 01:40:17.060
Yeah, I know, I know.

01:40:19.459 --> 01:40:21.336
But I love you.

01:40:30.930 --> 01:40:34.580
Who are you working for?
You didn't come up with all this by yourself.

01:40:34.685 --> 01:40:37.084
- You bastard!
- Nah, somebody's got to you.

01:40:37.187 --> 01:40:40.211
Somebody's paid you.
Speak a little Russian, do we?

01:40:41.359 --> 01:40:43.652
- Valentina! Scrumpy!
- Huh?

01:40:45.321 --> 01:40:47.511
Miraculous child, there you are.

01:40:47.616 --> 01:40:49.075
You old bastard.

01:40:49.180 --> 01:40:50.848
After everything we've been through.

01:40:50.952 --> 01:40:52.830
How could you? Is this how you repay me?

01:40:52.934 --> 01:40:55.229
I can't believe it. After everything.

01:40:55.333 --> 01:40:57.523
- And this is all your doing.
- Yeah, all my doing?

01:40:57.628 --> 01:40:59.505
- How could you, Doc?
- No, no, no, no, no.

01:40:59.609 --> 01:41:04.093
I'm Felicity. I-I mean I'm the falicitator -
the facilitator - dear boy.

01:41:04.197 --> 01:41:07.117
I create the opportunity.
It's not my fault if you're not up to it.

01:41:07.221 --> 01:41:09.516
I'll forgive you.

01:41:19.215 --> 01:41:20.570
Dad!

01:41:21.405 --> 01:41:23.281
Dad!

01:41:26.410 --> 01:41:27.766
Wake up.

01:41:27.871 --> 01:41:29.330
Dad!

01:41:29.434 --> 01:41:30.790
Please.

01:41:32.459 --> 01:41:34.648
- Please.
- Step back, miss. Step back.

01:41:36.213 --> 01:41:37.673
Sir? Can...?

01:41:38.925 --> 01:41:41.532
Please, miss. There's n-nothing you can do.

01:41:41.636 --> 01:41:43.826
- He's, he's d-d-dead...
- No!

01:41:43.930 --> 01:41:46.120
D-D-Dead drunk.

01:41:47.059 --> 01:41:49.561
- Bollocks.
- Haven't we seen this guy before?

01:41:49.666 --> 01:41:52.377
- Oh, they all look the same.
- Aye, bloody drunks.

01:41:56.862 --> 01:41:58.844
I hate you!

01:41:58.948 --> 01:42:01.033
You make me sick!

01:42:12.295 --> 01:42:14.277
This is to be my choice?

01:42:21.577 --> 01:42:25.018
Hold your horses.
There's absolutely no need for that.

01:42:25.123 --> 01:42:27.000
That's just plain contrariness.

01:42:27.105 --> 01:42:30.546
Oh, you really think you deserve punishment,
don't you?

01:42:31.277 --> 01:42:34.718
You have no idea. You're just a kid.

01:42:34.822 --> 01:42:35.655
Huh!

01:42:35.760 --> 01:42:38.368
Where have you been? I'm a woman now.

01:42:38.472 --> 01:42:40.767
Selfish bitch.

01:42:41.704 --> 01:42:45.042
- Only fit for...
- Only fit for Hell.

01:42:47.232 --> 01:42:49.214
If only.

01:42:50.882 --> 01:42:53.490
God, stop. Your pop'd never forgive me.

01:42:54.428 --> 01:42:55.991
That'd be a shame.

01:42:59.537 --> 01:43:00.893
Let's dance.

01:43:44.693 --> 01:43:45.841
Damn.

01:43:47.614 --> 01:43:49.177
I've won.

01:44:16.083 --> 01:44:20.672
You know it's... not exactly
what I had in mind, you know.

01:44:23.071 --> 01:44:24.948
All this.

01:44:25.051 --> 01:44:27.867
I mean, Valentina being the fifth.

01:44:29.223 --> 01:44:33.186
I mean, she's supposed to be the prize,
not part of the final score.

01:44:34.854 --> 01:44:36.836
Just doesn't seem fair.

01:44:39.130 --> 01:44:42.259
I hope they get that bastard
and tear him limb from limb.

01:44:42.362 --> 01:44:44.032
But they won't.

01:44:44.761 --> 01:44:46.743
He leads a charmed life, that one.

01:44:46.848 --> 01:44:48.308
Mm.

01:44:49.350 --> 01:44:51.540
I've been trying to get that bastard
for years.

01:44:51.645 --> 01:44:53.834
I thought I had him this time,
but, you know,

01:44:53.939 --> 01:44:56.963
some prat always seems
to come along and rescue him.

01:44:57.903 --> 01:44:59.257
Aargh!

01:45:00.822 --> 01:45:02.803
You know those er...

01:45:02.907 --> 01:45:06.245
weird markings that he had
on his forehead when you found him?

01:45:07.079 --> 01:45:08.956
What is all that about?

01:45:12.502 --> 01:45:14.379
Do they protect him or... What is it?

01:45:15.631 --> 01:45:18.030
I've never been into
all black magic stuff.

01:45:18.134 --> 01:45:20.114
I just couldn't get the hang of it.

01:45:22.617 --> 01:45:26.581
Can I offer you a stick of gum
or a breath mint?

01:45:28.562 --> 01:45:31.064
Oh, Jesus.
I hate to see you like this, Parny.

01:45:31.169 --> 01:45:32.630
I mean...

01:45:32.733 --> 01:45:34.714
I tell you what.

01:45:34.819 --> 01:45:38.260
If you can get me the lowdown
on all those satanic markings...

01:45:38.364 --> 01:45:42.015
Better, if you can help me wipe
that self-righteous little creep

01:45:42.119 --> 01:45:43.892
off the face of the universe...

01:45:44.623 --> 01:45:46.603
I'll give you Valentina back.

01:45:53.904 --> 01:45:55.885
What do you say?

01:46:01.099 --> 01:46:02.977
Oh!

01:46:03.081 --> 01:46:05.062
Thank God for that.

01:46:14.135 --> 01:46:15.074
Huh?

01:46:16.220 --> 01:46:17.159
Oh...

01:46:20.600 --> 01:46:22.582
Huh? Oh, shit.

01:46:22.687 --> 01:46:24.355
Give it to me.

01:46:24.459 --> 01:46:26.128
Oh, no.

01:46:26.232 --> 01:46:28.109
Look, I'm in a bit of a hurry.

01:46:28.214 --> 01:46:30.820
Now just give us a second, please, everybody.

01:46:33.740 --> 01:46:34.784
Oh!

01:46:34.887 --> 01:46:37.078
Here's your tube and there's mine.

01:46:37.183 --> 01:46:41.458
Mine's a cheap counterfeit, you know.
It breaks so easily.

01:46:43.231 --> 01:46:45.211
Oh, here's another.

01:46:46.047 --> 01:46:46.776
Stop!

01:46:46.880 --> 01:46:48.652
You're not amused?

01:46:48.757 --> 01:46:51.887
You've been talking to the Devil,
haven't you? What did he say?

01:46:51.991 --> 01:46:53.868
No, wait, let me.

01:46:53.972 --> 01:46:57.414
If you manage to kill me,
then he'll release Valentina, right?

01:46:58.770 --> 01:47:00.438
It's all lies. He can't release her.

01:47:00.543 --> 01:47:02.837
He can't release her
cos he doesn't have her.

01:47:02.941 --> 01:47:05.443
He doesn't have her
because she's the prize.

01:47:05.547 --> 01:47:07.425
He still doesn't have the five wins.

01:47:07.529 --> 01:47:09.511
But if you kill me, he will, won't he?

01:47:09.616 --> 01:47:11.805
Then you'll have lost Valentina forever.

01:47:11.910 --> 01:47:12.952
Choose.

01:47:13.057 --> 01:47:15.037
- This is ridiculous!
- Choose!

01:47:15.767 --> 01:47:16.498
Right.

01:47:21.816 --> 01:47:23.067
That one.

01:47:23.172 --> 01:47:25.049
Sure you made the right choice?

01:47:25.154 --> 01:47:27.135
Oh, look...

01:47:28.074 --> 01:47:29.742
Let's find out.

01:47:35.686 --> 01:47:36.938
VoilÃ .

01:47:47.575 --> 01:47:49.557
Jesus! Spit it out, you old goat.

01:47:55.292 --> 01:47:56.961
Gotcha!

01:48:06.034 --> 01:48:09.058
Thank you all for coming.
It's been a splendid success.

01:48:09.162 --> 01:48:10.621
Uh...

01:48:10.726 --> 01:48:12.499
Round the neck.

01:48:54.422 --> 01:48:56.090
Hey!

01:48:57.133 --> 01:49:00.784
There are three cardinal rules, Mr Nick.

01:49:01.722 --> 01:49:05.789
There is no black magic,
only cheap tricks.

01:49:06.519 --> 01:49:08.501
And I forget the others.

01:49:08.605 --> 01:49:11.212
Now where's my daughter?

01:49:11.317 --> 01:49:13.298
Oh, for Christ's sakes.

01:49:13.402 --> 01:49:15.280
How should I know?

01:49:15.383 --> 01:49:18.304
You're her father.
You're her loving father.

01:49:26.124 --> 01:49:28.002
I mean, she is free, isn't she?

01:49:28.941 --> 01:49:29.774
Jesus.

01:49:45.731 --> 01:49:47.607
<i>And the years roll on.</i>

01:49:49.484 --> 01:49:51.362
<i>Winds still blow.</i>

01:49:52.301 --> 01:49:54.178
<i>Snows still fall.</i>

01:49:54.282 --> 01:49:57.306
<i>Fires... still burn.</i>

01:49:59.288 --> 01:50:01.270
<i>And yet...</i>

01:50:01.373 --> 01:50:03.355
<i>everything has changed.</i>

01:50:05.649 --> 01:50:07.526
<i>Is that my punishment?</i>

01:50:10.446 --> 01:50:12.428
<i>Am I never to find her?</i>

01:50:30.782 --> 01:50:32.763
Please stop.

01:50:33.911 --> 01:50:35.788
No more choices.

01:50:36.830 --> 01:50:38.812
No more choices.

01:52:53.862 --> 01:52:55.844
So you found her?

01:52:55.948 --> 01:52:57.826
Yes.

01:52:58.973 --> 01:53:00.746
Yes, I found her.

01:53:03.039 --> 01:53:04.499
I think...

01:53:05.543 --> 01:53:07.524
...she may have a daughter.

01:53:08.670 --> 01:53:10.548
You're not going in there, are you?

01:53:13.051 --> 01:53:13.990
Er...

01:53:14.824 --> 01:53:17.639
You wouldn't want to scar a child
for life, would you?

01:53:18.891 --> 01:53:20.767
Look at you.

01:53:20.872 --> 01:53:22.854
No.

01:53:24.627 --> 01:53:25.879
Ohh.

01:53:26.816 --> 01:53:28.694
The Great Doctor Parnassus.

01:53:29.632 --> 01:53:31.927
You're an utter disgrace.

01:53:36.202 --> 01:53:37.871
This is gonna take some time.

01:53:37.975 --> 01:53:39.852
Oh, Percy.

01:53:40.999 --> 01:53:42.876
What would I do without you?

01:53:45.275 --> 01:53:47.257
Get a midget.

01:53:48.090 --> 01:53:51.012
Let Doctor Parnassus
open your imagination.

01:53:51.115 --> 01:53:54.348
Transcend heights
on Beauty's open wing

01:53:54.453 --> 01:53:57.477
and be transported to worlds
you've never dreamed of.

01:54:00.293 --> 01:54:02.275
Does it come with a happy ending?

01:54:03.526 --> 01:54:05.507
Sorry, we can't guarantee that.

01:54:12.076 --> 01:54:13.016
Ladies.

01:54:13.953 --> 01:54:15.831
God bless you, son.

01:54:24.904 --> 01:54:26.781
Get back to work.

